xpiks (1.3.1-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

    This release is highly polished and refactored in terms of thread-safety 
    Xpiks 1.3 with almost no new features, but switch from exiftool to exiv2.

    **In this release:**

    - full support for non-latin paths in Windows
    - Exiftool is not used by default anymore (but is optionally possible)
    - Portuguese and French localizations of interface
    - removing keywords duplicates when replacing with spelling suggestions
    - lots of improvements in thread-safety

    **Bugfixes:**

    - uploading of file with unicode path via curl
    - fix for selecting and double-clicking an image


 -- Artiom <a.mv@gmx.fr>  Mon, 30 May 2016 13:37:06 +0200

xpiks (1.2-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

    **Major features of this release:**

    - switching between list and grid view options
    - ability to explicitly attach vectors to previews
    - automatic exiftool detection for OS X users
    - upload progress reporting in taskbar on Windows
    - ability to correctly upload vectors to Dreamtimes (to the 'additional' directory)
    - larger description field in all popups
    - logs are now highlighted

